'''Peter Hartung''' (born&nbsp;{{circa}}&nbsp;1959) is the director of the [[Holocaust denial]] organization [[Adelaide Institute]] having previously been a successful businessman and political adviser. He is a native of [[Adelaide]], [[Australia]].

Hartung assumed the role of director of the Adelaide Institute in 2009, following the incarceration of [[Gerald Fredrick Töben]] for three months in [[South Australia]] for contempt of court.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/worldnews/article-1206280/Holocaust-denier-Frederick-Toben-centre-British-legal-row-jailed-months-Australia.html#ixzz1AWfFQ2sC | location=London | work=Daily Mail | first=Richard | last=Shears | title=Holocaust denier at centre of British legal row is jailed for three months in Australia | date=2009-08-13}}</ref> On assuming the role from Toben, Hartung defied the Federal Court by publishing the revisionist material that led to Toben’s three months jail time.<ref>{{cite news | title = Holocaust denier Peter Hartung in defiance of court | last = Akerman| first = Pia| work = The Australian | date = 2009-06-02 | url = http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/holocaust-denier-peter-hartung-in-defiance-of-court/story-e6frg6p6-1225720024851 | accessdate = 2011-06-13}}</ref>

